<subSubSection id="48D355CA8FEAFE6448A7528DFE2BF8D1" pageId="420" pageNumber="421" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418FEAFE6448A7528DFC5DF90D" blockId="420.[151,1436,1441,1970]" pageId="420" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538FEAFE6448A7528DFE31FA4A" bold="true" box="[151,404,1441,1466]" pageId="420" pageNumber="421">Description of female</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48FEAFE644A6C528DFD10FA49" box="[604,693,1441,1465]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="420" pageNumber="421" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
. Testaceous-reddish, except petiole black and antennal segment 10 brown. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 11:7:17:11:8:7:6:6:6:9. Head excavated, dull, granulated; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; POL = 1; OL = 5; OOL = 10. Palpal formula 6/3. Pronotum shiny, unsculptured, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, smooth, with two lateral points. Scutellum small, shiny, smooth.. Metanotum smooth, slightly longer than scutellum, hollow behind scutellum. Metathorax + propodeum shiny, with anterior surface unsculptured and posterior surface transversely striate. Mesopleuron and metapleuron transversely striate. Meso-metapleural suture distinct and complete. Fore tarsal segments in following proportions: 15:3:6:21:30. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FEAFE644B8851B1FB92F945" box="[952,1079,1693,1717]" captionStart="PLATE 132" captionStartId="421.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[228,1376,241,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-64@421.[190,1397,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="421" captionText="PLATE 132. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus thai (from Olmi 1984). B. G. viet (from Olmi 1986). C. G. viraktamathi (from Olmi 1987c). D. G.yasumatsui(from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.15 mm for B, 0.37 mm for C and 0.22 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278840/files/figure.png" pageId="420" pageNumber="421">Plate 132A</figureCitation>
) with one small subapical tooth and five peg-like hairs. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48FEAFE644A8551EDFC96F929" box="[693,819,1729,1753]" captionStart="PLATE 132" captionStartId="421.[151,234,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[228,1376,241,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-64@421.[190,1397,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="421" captionText="PLATE 132. Chelae, holotypes. A. Gonatopus thai (from Olmi 1984). B. G. viet (from Olmi 1986). C. G. viraktamathi (from Olmi 1987c). D. G.yasumatsui(from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.26 mm for A, 0.15 mm for B, 0.37 mm for C and 0.22 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278840/files/figure.png" pageId="420" pageNumber="421">Plate 132A</figureCitation>
) with inner margin proximally serrated, with two rows of about 30 lamellae; distal apex with about nine lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
